How to protect yourself?
Condoms can reduce the risk of infection, but they do not protect 100%.
The reason for this is that pathogens of sexually transmitted diseases can also be transmitted by lubricating infection or by close bodily contact.
Experts therefore recommend that anyone who changes sexual partners often undergo regular exams.
Most quickly detected ISTs can be cured and late sequels can be avoided.
