This is an ethnic qualification, just as my friends in Boston use when they call themselves "Irish", or my friends in New York when they call themselves "Italians".
Then I became "Mexico-American."
But here, it was Mexico.
And, on the land that my grandfather was born, there is no need for special qualifications or a trait of union.
I was just an American.
