The only reason that explains the large number of Mexican ancestors in cities like Los Angeles, Las Vegas, Phoenix, Denver or San Antonio, is that at some point, in our family tree, a person, perhaps a parent or grandparent, found no opportunity in Mexico and went into the North.
And most often, this person corresponded to a typical profile -- a dark skin, poorly educated, from a poor village, etc.
We are their descendants, and we are loyal to them.
Not in Mexico.
And even if we are currently living the American dream, that we have gone to good schools and we have good situations, we must never lose sight that it is the American dream that we live, and not that of Mexicans.
Our identity is sometimes disturbed, but our loyalty is obvious.
We agree with the United States.
