In addition, many Mexican-Americans that I know do not feel like being part of one country or the other.
We love the music of the Mexican band, Los Tigres del Norte, but also Bruce Springsteen.
We have the best of both worlds, but we are not rooted in either.
In Mexico, we are considered Americans.
And in the United States, we are considered Mexicans.
And now, to complicate the relationship a little more, as I learned during my stay, some Mexican leaders and part of the intelligences want to get closer to the Diaspora.
