“I didn’t write anything in this book that could hurt someone or affect him in any way,” he told the press at the time.
After his liver transplantation, he became an active organ donation activist and worked as a volunteer in a hospital to assist concerned patients.
“I advise them, I give them back confidence, I come with them when they come to have surgery and then,” he said in 1996.
I’m trying to offer them some comfort, like, “Don’t be afraid, it won’t be easy for a little while, but it’s going to be fine.”
